commit.message: Update dependencies

Created super rough README

Merge branch 'feature/player-controls'

Merging in the show/hide features because they look nice and add some necessary feedback for the user at this point.

Show/hide/autoplay update...

Had autoplay earlier tonight, but there were a lot of exceptional scenarios that would also allow the player to auto play. We need to figure out a way to only have it auto play on the first time attempting to playback content when the queue is empty and the player is not initialized.

However, the following HAVE been implemented:

- Show/hide player
- Alert user to add content to queue if empty when trying to begin playback or show an unintialized player
- Alert user to begin playback if the queue is not empty but the player is uninitialized
- Alert user if a song ends and there is no more music in the queue
- Alert user if they try to fastforward to the next song but there is no more music in the queue (this previously caused an error in the player if they tried to poll an empty queue)

Not pushing to master yet because this is some awk functionality that MAY (or may not) require some refactoring.
This change was suggested by Ryan to suppress unwanted "undefined" errors because the variable "player" is being overwritten in a separate file.
A way for us to handle if the queue is empty from the server side.
Refactor: change "testLog()" to "addToQueue()". The previous name was misleading and made it seem like the function was less important than it really is.
Refactor: change "slidePlayer()" to "showOrHidePlayer()".
Got hide/show functionality without awkward repositioning. Also alerts if there is no player instantiated yet. Not sure if we want that alert in that situation.
Fixed remaining merge conflict with logo positioning.
